  16832  3月 26 15:06 heartbeat.md\n-rw-rw-r--  1 zhangyanbo zhangyanbo   8541  3月 26 15:06 index.md\n-rw-rw-r--  1 zhangyanbo zhangyanbo   5404  3月 26 15:06 local-models.md\n-rw-rw-r--  1 zhangyanbo zhangyanbo   4125  3月 26 15:06 logging.md\n-rw-rw-r--  1 zhangyanbo zhangyanbo   3517  3月 26 15:06 multiple-gateways.md\n-rw-rw-r--  1 zhangyanbo zhangyanbo   1533  3月 26 15:06 network-model.md\n-rw-rw-r--  1 zhangyanbo zhangyanbo   7891  3月 26 15:06 openai-http-api.md\n-rw-rw-r--  1 zhangyanbo zhangyanbo   9004  3月 26 15:06 openresponses-http-api.md\n-rw-rw-r--  1 zhangyanbo zhangyanbo   9639  3月 26 15:06 openshell.md\n-rw-rw-r--  1 zhangyanbo zhangyanbo   3475  3月 26 15:06 pairing.md\n-rw-rw-r--  1 zhangyanbo zhangyanbo   9661  3月 26 15:06 protocol.md\n-rw-rw-r--  1 zhangyanbo zhangyanbo   3777  3月 26 15:06 remote-gateway-readme.md\n-rw-rw-r--  1 zhangyanbo zhangyanbo   7221  3月 26 15:06 remote.md\n-rw-rw-r--  1 zhangyanbo zhangyanbo  20081  3月 26 15:06 sandboxing.md\n-rw-rw-r--  1 zhangyanbo zhangyanbo   5642  3月 26 15:06 sandbox-vs-tool-policy-vs-elevated.md\n-rw-rw-r--  1 zhangyanbo zhangyanbo  17628  3月 26 15:06 secrets.md\n-rw-rw-r--  1 zhangyanbo zhangyanbo   3942  3月 26 15:06 secrets-plan-contract.md\ndrwxrwxr-x  2 zhangyanbo zhangyanbo   4096  3月 26 15:06 security\n-rw-rw-r--  1 zhangyanbo zhangyanbo   4845  3月 26 15:06 tailscale.md\n-rw-rw-r--  1 zhangyanbo zhangyanbo   4239  3月 26 15:06 tools-invoke-http-api.md\n-rw-rw-r--  1 zhangyanbo zhangyanbo  12920  3月 26 15:06 troubleshooting.md\n-rw-rw-r--  1 zhangyanbo zhangyanbo  10552  3月 26 15:06 trusted-proxy-auth.md","cwd":"/home/zhangyanbo/.openclaw/workspace-fox-avatar"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774510218353}}
{"type":"message","id":"b5fc20a9","parentId":"09549d49","timestamp":"2026-03-26T07:30:31.796Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"用户想要更详细地了解 Gateway / OpenAI 兼容性的功能。我看到有一个 `openai-http-api.md` 文件，应该有更详细的信息。让我读取它。","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_3671a270247b401ebc75209a","name":"read","arguments":{"file":"/home/zhangyanbo/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/openai-http-api.md"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"zai","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":24695,"output":108,"cacheRead":3008,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":27811,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774510218357,"responseId":"2026032615301837307630afe743c0"}}
{"type":"message","id":"3de02336","parentId":"b5fc20a9","timestamp":"2026-03-26T07:30:31.822Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_3671a270247b401ebc75209a","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nsummary: \"Expose an OpenAI-compatible /v1/chat/completions HTTP endpoint from the Gateway\"\nread_when:\n  - Integrating tools that expect OpenAI Chat Completions\ntitle: \"OpenAI Chat Completions\"\n---\n\n# OpenAI Chat Completions (HTTP)\n\nOpenClaw’s Gateway can serve a small OpenAI-compatible Chat Completions endpoint.\n\nThis endpoint is **disabled by default**. Enable it in config first.\n\n- `POST /v1/chat/completions`\n- Same port as the Gateway (WS + HTTP multiplex): `http://<gateway-host>:<port>/v1/chat/completions`\n\nWhen the Gateway’s OpenAI-compatible HTTP surface is enabled, it also serves:\n\n- `GET /v1/models`\n- `GET /v1/models/{id}`\n- `POST /v1/embeddings`\n- `POST /v1/responses`\n\nUnder the hood, requests are executed as a normal Gateway agent run (same codepath as `openclaw agent`), so routing/permissions/config match your Gateway.\n\n## Authentication\n\nUses the Gateway auth configuration. Send a bearer token:\n\n- `Authorization: Bearer <token>`\n\nNotes:\n\n- When `gateway.auth.mode=\"token\"`, use `gateway.auth.token` (or `OPENCLAW_GATEWAY_TOKEN`).\n- When `gateway.auth.mode=\"password\"`, use `gateway.auth.password` (or `OPENCLAW_GATEWAY_PASSWORD`).\n- If `gateway.auth.rateLimit` is configured and too many auth failures occur, the endpoint returns `429` with `Retry-After`.\n\n## Security boundary (important)\n\nTreat this endpoint as a **full operator-access** surface for the gateway instance.\n\n- HTTP bearer auth here is not a narrow per-user scope model.\n- A valid Gateway token/password for this endpoint should be treated like an owner/operator credential.\n- Requests run through the same control-plane agent path as trusted operator actions.\n- There is no separate non-owner/per-user tool boundary on this endpoint; once a caller passes Gateway auth here, OpenClaw treats that caller as a trusted operator for this gateway.\n- If the target agent policy allows sensitive tools, this endpoint can use them.\n- Keep this endpoint on loopback/tailnet/private ingress only; do not expose it directly to the public internet.\n\nSee [Security](/gateway/security) and [Remote access](/gateway/remote).\n\n## Agent-first model contract\n\nOpenClaw treats the OpenAI `model` field as an **agent target**, not a raw provider model id.\n\n- `model: \"openclaw\"` routes to the configured default agent.\n- `model: \"openclaw/default\"` also routes to the configured default agent.\n- `model: \"openclaw/<agentId>\"` routes to a specific agent.\n\nOptional request headers:\n\n- `x-openclaw-model: <provider/model-or-bare-id>` overrides the backend model for the selected agent.\n- `x-openclaw-agent-id: <agentId>` remains supported as a compatibility override.\n- `x-openclaw-session-key: <sessionKey>` fully controls session routing.\n- `x-openclaw-message-channel: <channel>` sets the synthetic ingress channel context for channel-aware prompts and policies.\n\nCompatibility aliases still accepted:\n\n- `model: \"openclaw:<agentId>\"`\n- `model: \"agent:<agentId>\"`\n\n## Enabling the endpoint\n\nSet `gateway.http.endpoints.chatCompletions.enabled` to `true`:\n\n```json5\n{\n  gateway: {\n    http: {\n      endpoints: {\n        chatCompletions: { enabled: true },\n      },\n    },\n  },\n}\n```\n\n## Disabling the endpoint\n\nSet `gateway.http.endpoints.chatCompletions.enabled` to `false`:\n\n```json5\n{\n  gateway: {\n    http: {\n      endpoints: {\n        chatCompletions: { enabled: false },\n      },\n    },\n  },\n}\n```\n\n## Session behavior\n\nBy default the endpoint is **stateless per request** (a new session key is generated each call).\n\nIf the request includes an OpenAI `user` string, the Gateway derives a stable session key from it, so repeated calls can share an agent session.\n\n## Why this surface matters\n\nThis is the highest-leverage compatibility set for self-hosted frontends and tooling:\n\n- Most Open WebUI, LobeChat, and LibreChat setups expect `/v1/models`.\n- Many RAG systems expect `/v1/embeddings`.\n- Existing OpenAI chat clients can usually start with `/v1/chat/completions`.\n- More agent-native clients increasingly prefer `/v1/responses`.\n\n## Model list and agent routing\n\n<AccordionGroup>\n  <Accordion title=\"What does `/v1/models` return?\">\n    An OpenClaw agent-target list.\n\n    The returned ids are `openclaw`, `openclaw/default`, and `openclaw/<agentId>` entries.\n    Use them directly as OpenAI `model` values.\n\n  </Accordion>\n  <Accordion title=\"Does `/v1/models` list agents or sub-agents?\">\n    It lists top-level agent targets, not backend provider models and not sub-agents.\n\n    Sub-agents remain internal execution topology. They do not appear as pseudo-models.\n\n  </Accordion>\n  <Accordion title=\"Why is `openclaw/default` included?\">\n    `openclaw/default` is the stable alias for the configured default agent.\n\n    That means clients can keep using one predictable id even if the real default agent id changes between environments.\n\n  </Accordion>\n  <Accordion title=\"How do I override the backend model?\">\n    Use `x-openclaw-model`.\n\n    Examples:\n    `x-openclaw-model: openai/gpt-5.4`\n    `x-openclaw-model: gpt-5.4`\n\n    If you omit it, the selected agent runs with its normal configured model choice.\n\n  </Accordion>\n  <Accordion title=\"How do embeddings fit this contract?\">\n    `/v1/embeddings` uses the same agent-target `model` ids.\n\n    Use `model: \"openclaw/default\"` or `model: \"openclaw/<agentId>\"`.\n    When you need a specific embedding model, send it in `x-openclaw-model`.\n    Without that header, the request passes through to the selected agent's normal embedding setup.\n\n  </Accordion>\n</AccordionGroup>\n\n## Streaming (SSE)\n\nSet `stream: true` to receive Server-Sent Events (SSE):\n\n- `Content-Type: text/event-stream`\n- Each event line is `data: <json>`\n- Stream ends with `data: [DONE]`\n\n## Open WebUI quick setup\n\nFor a basic Open WebUI connection:\n\n- Base URL: `http://127.0.0.1:18789/v1`\n- Docker on macOS base URL: `http://host.docker.internal:18789/v1`\n- API key: your Gateway bearer token\n- Model: `openclaw/default`\n\nExpected behavior:\n\n- `GET /v1/models` should list `openclaw/default`\n- Open WebUI should use `openclaw/default` as the chat model id\n- If you want a specific backend provider/model for that agent, set the agent's normal default model or send `x-openclaw-model`\n\nQuick smoke:\n\n```bash\ncurl -sS http://127.0.0.1:18789/v1/models \\\n  -H 'Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN'\n```\n\nIf that returns `openclaw/default`, most Open WebUI setups can connect with the same base URL and token.\n\n## Examples\n\nNon-streaming:\n\n```bash\ncurl -sS http://127.0.0.1:18789/v1/chat/completions \\\n  -H 'Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN' \\\n  -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \\\n  -d '{\n    \"model\": \"openclaw/default\",\n    \"messages\": [{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"hi\"}]\n  }'\n```\n\nStreaming:\n\n```bash\ncurl -N http://127.0.0.1:18789/v1/chat/completions \\\n  -H 'Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN' \\\n  -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \\\n  -H 'x-openclaw-model: openai/gpt-5.4' \\\n  -d '{\n    \"model\": \"openclaw/research\",\n    \"stream\": true,\n    \"messages\": [{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"hi\"}]\n  }'\n```\n\nList models:\n\n```bash\ncurl -sS http://127.0.0.1:18789/v1/models \\\n  -H 'Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN'\n```\n\nFetch one model:\n\n```bash\ncurl -sS http://127.0.0.1:18789/v1/models/openclaw%2Fdefault \\\n  -H 'Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN'\n```\n\nCreate embeddings:\n\n```bash\ncurl -sS http://127.0.0.1:18789/v1/embeddings \\\n  -H 'Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN' \\\n  -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \\\n  -H 'x-openclaw-model: openai/text-embedding-3-small' \\\n  -d '{\n    \"model\": \"openclaw/default\",\n    \"input\": [\"alpha\", \"beta\"]\n  }'\n```\n\nNotes:\n\n- `/v1/models` returns OpenClaw agent targets, not raw provider catalogs.\n- `openclaw/default` is always present so one stable id works across environments.\n- Backend provider/model overrides belong in `x-openclaw-model`, not the OpenAI `model` field.\n- `/v1/embeddings` supports `input` as a string or array of strings.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774510231820}}
{"type":"message","id":"eb1b42dc","parentId":"3de02336","timestamp":"2026-03-26T07:31:08.084Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"用户想要了解 Gateway / OpenAI 兼容性的详细信息。我已经读取了相关文档，现在可以给出详细的解释。","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"好的，这是 3.24 版本中 **Gateway / OpenAI 兼容性** 的详细讲解：\n\n---\n\n## 🎯 核心概念\n\nOpenClaw Gateway 现在提供了一套 **OpenAI 兼容的 HTTP API**，让任何支持 OpenAI API 的前端/工具都能直接连接 OpenClaw。\n\n### 提供的接口\n\n| 接口 | 用途 |\n|------|------|\n| `GET /v1/models` | 列出可用的 agent |\n| `GET /v1/models/{id}` | 获取单个 agent 信息 |\n| `POST /v1/embeddings` | 文本嵌入（RAG/记忆系统用） |\n| `POST /v1/chat/completions` | 聊天对话（主流客户端用） |\n| `POST /v1/responses` | Agent 原生响应（新标准） |\n\n---\n\n## 🤖 Agent-First 模型路由\n\n**关键点：`model` 字段不是模型 ID，而是 agent ID！**\n\n```\nmodel: \"openclaw\"          → 路由到默认 agent\nmodel: \"openclaw/default\"  → 同上，稳定别名\nmodel: \"openclaw/research\" → 路由到名为 \"research\" 的 agent\n```\n\n### 想覆盖后端模型？\n\n用 `x-openclaw-model` 请求头：\n\n```bash\ncurl http://127.0.0.1:18789/v1/chat/completions \\\n  -H 'Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN' \\\n  -H 'x-openclaw-model: openai/gpt-5.4' \\\n  -d '{\"model\": \"openclaw/default\", \"messages\": [...]}'\n```\n\n这样就能用指定 agent 的配置 + 指定的后端模型。\n\n---\n\n## 🔧 如何启用\n\n默认是**关闭**的，需要在配置中开启：\n\n```json5\n{\n  gateway: {\n    http: {\n      endpoints: {\n        chatCompletions: { enabled: true },\n      },\n    },\n  },\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 🔒 安全边界\n\n**重要：这个端点等同于完整的 operator 权限！**\n\n- 通过 Gateway 认证 = 拥有者/操作员权限\n- 没有独立的用户隔离\n- 如果 agent 配置允许敏感工具，这个端点也能用\n- **只绑定 loopback / Tailscale / 内网**，不要直接暴露到公网\n\n---\n\n## 📦 实际应用场景\n\n### Open WebUI / LobeChat / LibreChat\n\n这些前端通常会先探测 `/v1/models`，然后用返回的 model id 发起聊天。\n\n**配置示例：**\n\n```\nBase URL:  http://127.0.0.1:18789/v1\nAPI Key:   你的 Gateway token\nModel:     openclaw/default\n```\n\n### RAG / 记忆系统\n\n很多 RAG pipeline 需要 `/v1/embeddings` 接口，现在可以直接对接：\n\n```bash\ncurl http://127.0.0.1:18789/v1/embeddings \\\n  -H 'Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN' \\\n  -H 'x-openclaw-model: openai/text-embedding-3-small' \\\n  -d '{\"model\": \"openclaw/default\", \"input\": [\"文本1\", \"文本2\"]}'\n```\n\n---\n\n## 📝 示例调用\n\n**非流式：**\n```bash\ncurl http://127.0.0.1:18789/v1/chat/completions \\\n  -H 'Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN' \\\n  -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \\\n  -d '{\n    \"model\": \"openclaw/default\",\n    \"messages\": [{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"你好\"}]\n  }'\n```\n\n**流式（SSE）：**\n```bash\ncurl -N http://127.0.0.1:18789/v1/chat/completions \\\n  -H 'Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN' \\\n  -d '{\"model\": \"openclaw/default\", \"stream\": true, \"messages\": [...]}'\n```\n\n---\n\n简单说，这个更新让 OpenClaw 能**无缝对接整个 OpenAI 生态**——你现有的 Open WebUI、LobeChat、RAG 工具基本都能直接连上来用 🎉"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"zai","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":5577,"output":993,"cacheRead":24256,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":30826,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774510231822,"responseId":"202603261530319a732bc2d2554907"}}
